11 Sec. 7. 36 MRSA §5403, sub-§1, as enacted by PL 2015, c. 267, Pt. DD, §33, is
22 repealed and the following enacted in its place:
3 1. Individual income tax rate tables. Beginning in 2025 and each year thereafter, by
4 the dollar amounts of the tax rate tables specified in section 5111, subsections 1-G, 2-G
5 and 3-G, except that for the purposes of this subsection, notwithstanding section 5402,
6 subsection 1-B, the "cost-of-living adjustment" is the Chained Consumer Price Index for
7 the 12-month period ending June 30th of the preceding calendar year divided by the
8 Chained Consumer Price Index for the 12-month period ending June 30, 2024;
9 SUMMARY
1100 This bill changes, beginning in 2026, the current income tax brackets by increasing the
1111 threshold amount of income subject to the current tax rates of 5.8%, 6.75% and 7.15%.
1122 The bill adds 3 new income tax brackets and imposes tax rates of 7.52%, 7.15% and 8.2%
1133 in those new brackets. As under current law, the income tax brackets are indexed to the
1144 Chained Consumer Price Index as published by the United States Department of Labor,
1155 Bureau of Labor Statistics.
